<div id="review_3406286682" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3406286682" />
    <a title="Eswar" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12705827-eswar"><img alt="Eswar" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1358106362p2/12705827.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3406286682?book_show_action=true">Mar 04, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Eswar" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Eswar" href="/user/show/12705827-eswar">Eswar</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3406286682" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10301660630210051120">A great primer into why the Montessori education process is so focused on the child first. Book reiterated over and over why adults should take a step back, be cautious about our actions and wording when communicating physically or verbally. All children will see adults as role-model. Key is to not get in the way, let them be children and focus on children first. Today&apos;s environment tries to pigeon-hole children&apos;s educational needs with adult&apos;s priority first (day care rather than education). Gi</span>
  <span id="freeText10301660630210051120" style="display:none">A great primer into why the Montessori education process is so focused on the child first. Book reiterated over and over why adults should take a step back, be cautious about our actions and wording when communicating physically or verbally. All children will see adults as role-model. Key is to not get in the way, let them be children and focus on children first. Today's environment tries to pigeon-hole children's educational needs with adult's priority first (day care rather than education). Given that children in a sensitive period (3-6) will be affected by anything parents do, we need to ensure nothing becomes a trauma. Don't push for anything, but let them be first.<br /><br />Today I let my daughter decide whether she wanted to go to school or not, she got ready by herself and had her lead the way to school, rather than me rushing her along. This was inspired by this book.<br /><br />It's only human being adults that impose their view on their children before pushing them into society as quickly as possible. Other animals shelter their child until they are ready for the rest of society. Nudging rather than forcing them out into the world stage.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10301660630210051120" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


